<div type="abstract"><head>Rat an Ludwig XI., Graf von Oettingen, Hofmeister König Sigismunds</head><p>Der Rat teilt mit, dass zwar die Schafe auf dem Hesselberg bei Wittelshofen dem H. Gummler, Bürger zu Nürnberg, gehören, der Schäfer jedoch einigen Dinkelsbühlern zu versprechen stehe.</p>
</div>
<!--This div could possibly contain the analytic portion of the edition.-->
<div type="linguisticAnalysis"><ab><w join="" lemma="" msd="" part="" pos=""><fLib><f name=" "/></fLib></w></ab></div>
</front>
<body><div type="diplomatic"><pb facs="#facs_312" id="155r"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee"><ab facs="#facs_312_r1l23"><expan>H<ex>er</ex>n</expan> ludweıg dem <expan>elt<ex>er</ex>n</expan> <expan>graf<ex>en</ex></expan> ʒu <expan>Ötıng<ex>en</ex></expan> <expan>hofmeıſt<ex>er</ex></expan> etc </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content"><ab facs="#facs_312_r1l24"><expan>Gneͣdıg<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>h<ex>er</ex>re</expan> als vns eẅr gnad <expan>verſchr<ex>iben</ex></expan> hat von des handels <expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_312_r1l26">der ſıch <expan>ʒwıſche<ex>n</ex></expan>
<add><ab facs="#facs_312_line_1577276590065_97">etlıchen </ab></add> den <expan>eẅ<ex>r</ex>n</expan> vnd <expan>eine<ex>n</ex></expan> ſcheͣfer ʒu wyttelſhofen an </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_312_r1l27">dem <expan>Oſelb<ex>er</ex>g</expan> <expan>ergang<ex>en</ex></expan> hab / <expan>Derſ<ex>elb</ex></expan> ſcheffer <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>m</expan> <expan>b<ex>urger</ex></expan> ~ dem <expan>gum<ex>m</ex>ler</expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_312_r1l28">ʒugehörn ſülle etc / das <expan>habe<ex>n</ex></expan> wır wol <expan>vernom<ex>en</ex></expan> / Vnd <expan>eẅ<ex>r</ex>n</expan> <expan>gnad<ex>en</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_312_r1l29">ʒu lıeb haben wır <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>n</expan> <expan>b<ex>urger</ex></expan> ~ den <expan>Gum<ex>m</ex>ler</expan> für vns beſandt vnd </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_312_r1l30"><expan>daru<ex>m</ex>b</expan> ʒurede geſacʒt . Der hat vns <expan>geantw<ex>ur</ex>t</expan> . wıe dıe ſchaffe </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_312_r1l32">daſelbs ſein ſeyn / aber den ſcheffer 
<add><ab facs="#facs_312_line_1577276604687_111">da </ab></add> <expan>v<ex>er</ex>antwurt</expan> er nıht vnd ſtee </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_312_r1l33">Jm auch niht <expan>ʒuu<ex>er</ex>ſprechen</expan> . <expan>ſund<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>derſ<ex>elb</ex></expan> <expan>ſcheff<ex>er</ex></expan> ſtee <expan>etlıche<ex>n</ex></expan> <expan>leẅt<ex>en</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_312_r1l34">ʒu dınkelſpühel <expan>ʒuu<ex>er</ex>ſprechen</expan>
<add><ab facs="#facs_312_r1l37">als er mayne </ab></add> Denn wo wır <expan>eẅ<ex>r</ex>n</expan> <expan>gnad<ex>en</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_312_line_1577276620995_128">lıeb <expan>od<ex>er</ex></expan> dıenſt etc <expan>dat<ex>um</ex></expan> <expan>f<ex>er</ex>ıa</expan> ıııȷ<hi rend="sup">a</hi> <expan>p<ex>oſt</ex></expan> Bartholomeȷ </ab>
</div>
</div><div type="regularised"><pb facs="#facs_312" id="155r"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee">
<ab><expan>H<ex>er</ex>n</expan> Ludweig dem <expan>elt<ex>er</ex>n</expan>,
                                <expan>graf<ex>en</ex></expan> zu <expan>Öting<ex>en</ex></expan>,
                                <expan>hofmeist<ex>er</ex></expan> etc.</ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab><expan>Gneͣdig<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>h<ex>er</ex>re</expan>, als uns ewr gnad
                            <expan>verschr<ex>iben</ex></expan> hat von des handels
                                <expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan>, der sich
                            <expan>zwische<ex>n</ex></expan>
<add>etlichen</add> den <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>n</expan> und
                                <expan>eine<ex>m</ex></expan> scheͣfer zu Wyttelshofen an dem
                                <expan>Oselb<ex>er</ex>g</expan>
<expan>ergang<ex>en</ex></expan> hab, <expan>ders<ex>elb</ex></expan>
                        scheffer, <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>m</expan>
<expan>b<ex>urger</ex></expan> dem <expan>Gum<ex>m</ex>ler</expan> zugehörn
                        sülle etc., das <expan>habe<ex>n</ex></expan> wir wol
                                <expan>vernom<ex>en</ex></expan>. Und <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>n</expan>
<expan>gnad<ex>en</ex></expan> zu lieb haben wir
                            <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
<expan>b<ex>urger</ex></expan> den <expan>Gum<ex>m</ex>ler</expan> für uns
                        besandt und <expan>daru<ex>m</ex>b</expan> zurede gesaczt; der hat uns
                                <expan>geantw<ex>ur</ex>t</expan>, wie die schaffe daselbs sein
                        seyn, aber den scheffer <add>da</add>
<expan>v<ex>er</ex>antwurt</expan> er niht und stee im auch niht <expan>zu
                                v<ex>er</ex>sprechen</expan>, <expan>sund<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>ders<ex>elb</ex></expan>
<expan>scheff<ex>er</ex></expan> stee <expan>etliche<ex>n</ex></expan>
<expan>lewt<ex>en</ex></expan> zu Dinkelspühel <expan>zu
                            v<ex>er</ex>sprechen</expan>, <add>als er mayne</add>. Denn wo wir
                                <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>n</expan>
<expan>gnad<ex>en</ex></expan> lieb <expan>od<ex>er</ex></expan> dienst etc.
                                <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan>
<expan>f<ex>er</ex>ia</expan> iiii<hi rend="sup">a</hi>
<expan>p<ex>ost</ex></expan> Bartholomei.</ab>
</div>
</div></body>
